        <updateDate>2022-01-24T21:48:18Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Border Wall Reimbursement Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the federal government to reimburse a border state for amounts that state has expended on the construction of a border security wall in support of federal efforts. </p> <p>To receive reimbursement, a state must submit within 180 days of the bill's enactment an accounting of the expenses incurred by the state and its municipalities and the total sum of such expenses.</p> <p>Certain funds made available to assist states and local governments during the COVID-19 public health emergency may also be made available to reimburse border states under this bill. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
